annotationA: Cytochrome c-1; Electron carrier protein. The oxidized form of the cytochrome c heme group can accept an electron from the heme group of the cytochrome c1 subunit of cytochrome reductase. Cytochrome c then transfers this electron to the cytochrome oxidase complex, the final protein carrier in the mitochondrial electron-transport chain
annotationB: Cytochrome-c oxidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitochondrial electron transport, cytochrome c to oxygen
